// @test regression/plot-hline-arithmetic
// @description plot()/hline() return opaque handle types ("plot"/"hline") that carry no qualifier and cannot participate in arithmetic/comparison. They were typed "unknown" (so any operator was allowed); now mapped to real types and barred. Using a plot handle in fill() stays clean (its proper use). v6 only - legacy scripts stay lenient (see INV089 / the v4 gate). Probed 2026-06-25 via pine-lint --tv.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=7, message=/Cannot call "operator \+" with argument "expr0"="x".*"plot".*"const int"/
// @expects error: line=8, message=/Cannot call "operator \*" with argument "expr0"="h".*"hline".*"const int"/
// @expects errors: 2

//@version=6
indicator("plot-hline-arithmetic")
x = plot(close)
p2 = plot(open)
fill(x, p2, color.new(color.blue, 90))
h = hline(0)
plot(x + 1)
plot(h * 2)
